                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13988822" author="brandon.williams" created="Sat, 3 May 2014 22:02:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The main problem here was range xfers were not being deleted correctly, so it saw the token didn&apos;t need moving and just kept looping over it.  Cleaned up some log messages as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13988835" author="brandon.williams" created="Sat, 3 May 2014 22:49:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We also need to shutdown the scheduler when it&apos;s done since it doesn&apos;t need to hang around forever, I&apos;ll add this later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989678" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 16:33:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shutting down the scheduler from inside the task is difficult, so instead I adjusted the log message to tell the user to disable range xfers when there&apos;s nothing left to do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989685" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 16:47:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13989692" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 5 May 2014 16:53:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13994030" author="rhatch" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 23:07:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;duplicated the bug by running shuffle on the commit before, verified the fix by running shuffle on the fix commit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m updating dtests so they will watch for the log message above going forward when they run shuffle.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
